    <text type="petition">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01027.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">

                <div2 type="document">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A Smith</persName>, Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></salute>
                        <salute>Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Miss <persName>Matilda Harrington</persName>, now of the State of <placeName>Virginia</placeName>, having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned, &amp; having refused or neglected to file in your office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th Section of the Act of Congress, entitled "An act for the "release of certain persons held to service or labor in said <placeName>District</placeName>" approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16 1862</date>, you will please file this petition or schedule in lieu thereof, in pursuance of the provisions of an act supplementary said act which said last mentioned act was approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12 1862</date>." The Petitioner further states that the undersigned has resided in said <placeName>District</placeName> by &amp; with the consent of the said Miss <persName>Matilda Harrington</persName> from her early childhood.</p>
                    <ab>Name <persName>Jane Butler</persName>. Aged about 52 years. Sex Female. Remarks Dark color. height 5 ft 2 in</ab>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Jane Butler</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                        <signed><persName>Elizabeth B. McCormick</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>                        
                                        
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01027.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>paid</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Jane Butler</persName></ab>
                        <ab>Schedule</ab>
                        <ab>Amended Act <date when="1862-07-12">July 12th 1862</date></ab>
                        <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> given</ab>
                        <ab><choice><abbr>Idfd</abbr><expan>Identified</expan></choice> by Mrs <persName>Elizabeth McCormick</persName></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folios 90 &amp; 91.</ab>                        
                    </div3>
                                       
                    <div3 type="section">         
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-08-02">Aug. 2d 1862</date></ab>
                        <p>The Commissioners, satisfied on the testimony of Mrs <persName>Elizabeth McCormick</persName>, of the truth of the within statement, order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>Dist. of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk <choice><abbr>Emn</abbr><expan>Emancipation</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>Comn</abbr><expan>Commissioners</expan></choice></signed>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-08-02">Aug 2, 1862</date></dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>                    
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01027.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                
                <dateline><date when="1862-08-02">Aug 2</date></dateline>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Jane Butler</persName> servant of <persName>Matilda Harrington</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Elizabeth McCormick</persName>. I know this servant <persName>Jane</persName> &amp; have for upwards of 3 years as property of <persName>Mrs Harrington</persName>. She was here on <date when="1862-04-16">16 Apl</date>. <persName>Mrs Harrington</persName> left her here when <persName>Mrs Harrington</persName> went to <placeName>Westmoreland Co Va</placeName> she was here with <persName>Mrs Harringtons</persName> knowledge &amp; consent</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> ordered</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                <ab>230</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01027.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Jane Butler</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-08-02">Aug 2</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
